      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i was looking at my mortgage statement and it's super confusing. i have a 30 year fixed at 6.5% on a $400,000 loan. i know my monthly payment is roughly $2528 but i'm trying to figure out how much of that is actually hitting the principal vs interest. like, if i look at year 5 compared to year 25, is there a huge difference in how much interest i'm paying each month? can u break down how that actually works?",
