      "content": "Yes, you will see a significant difference between year 5 and year 25 regarding how much of your payment goes to interest versus principal. In the early years of a fixed-rate mortgage, the majority of your monthly payment is allocated to interest because the outstanding principal balance is very high. As you pay down the loan over time, the amount of interest due each month decreases, meaning more of your fixed payment starts tackling the principal.",
